        <p>VP of Engineering at a publicly traded software company, three-year tenure, $320K base salary, $180K annual RSU vest (mostly time-based), $80K annual cash bonus with a consistent two-year history. Two big banks looked at the $320K W-2 base, hesitated on the RSU income, treated the bonus as discretionary, and capped the offer at $1.1M. We pulled the grant letters, the vesting schedule, the W-2s showing two-year bonus history, and the brokerage statements with vested-share values. Ran the Fannie Mae 200-day moving average for RSU income calculation. Two-year bonus average added properly. Total qualifying income: $580K. Routed to a jumbo lender comfortable with equity-heavy executive files. Approved at $1.7M for a Pinecrest home with a pool. Closed in 31 days. The right loan program existed the whole time &mdash; the first two banks just didn&rsquo;t know how to read an SVP-tier executive file.</p>
